verbose_text: It is important to note that there was no difference in the Fgfr1 expression between Hs2st -/- and Hs6st1 -/- with WT (XREF_FIG N-P), suggesting that the difference in pErk found in Hs2st -/- and Hs6st1 -/- (XREF_FIG Q-S) are driven by the co-receptor function of HS, which in turn is differentially regulated by Hs2st and Hs6st1.
evidence: Hs6st1 -/-  ( XREF_FIG Q-S) are driven by the co-receptor function of HS
